<br>
And what is it about the 1st Amendment that leads so many to completely fail to see why it was included in the Bill of Rights.  Free speech does not let you say what you want without discussion... it encourages <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>quite</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> the opposite.  <br>
<br>
I just HATE rhetorical dilettantes who want not to exchange ideas, but merely want to be <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>right</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->. The hypocrisy these people use when they cop this attitude and then proceed to call everyone <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>else</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->&quot;Ignorant&quot; for not letting them politely have their opinion, unchallenged, is <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>sickening</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.  Sorry, but if you don't want your opinion criticized by those who disagree, <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>keep it to yourself</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.  And <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>don't ever</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> bring it into a forum specifically designed for people who love to debate.  <br>
<br>
